question: What are genes related to Cone dystrophy?
agent_answer:
The genes related to Cone dystrophy are:

1. [GUCA1A](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:4678)
2. [KCNV2](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:19698)
3. [CACNA2D4](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:20202)
4. [PDE6C](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:8787)
5. [CNGB3](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:2153)
6. [GNAT2](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:4394)

These genes are associated with Cone dystrophy and may play a role in the development or progression of the disease.
